<back>
<div type="commentary">
<p>Ossuary has vaulted lid with base broadened into cornice of length 54 cm and width 35 cm. Height describes height of chest plus that of lid. Part of rim and wall of chest's right side were repaired in antiquity with iron rivet. Ornamentation consists of one raised rectangle resembling an ashlar on the chest's front and back side, and one raised rhomb on the chest's left side. Inscription is on lid. ישוע is a contraction of יהושע, and דוסתס is a contraction of the common name Dositheos.</p>
</div>
